         <abstract>
            <p>Summation of series of the form ∑&lt;sup&gt;∞&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;k = 1&lt;/sub&gt; k&lt;sup&gt;ν - 1&lt;/sup&gt;r(k) is considered, where 0 ≤ ν ≤ 1 and r is a rational function. By an application of the Euler-Maclaurin summation formula, the problem is reduced to the evaluation of Gauss' hypergeometric function. Examples are given.</p>
          </abstract>
